definitions.definition: An unimportant individual in a greater system.
( carpentry ) A projection or tenon at the end of a beam designed to fit into a matching opening of another piece of wood to form a joint .
( mining ) One of the rough pillars of stone or coal left to support the roof of a mine.

definitions.definition: ( historical ) A partially clinker-built , flat - bottomed , square-rigged mediaeval ship of burden or war , with a round , bulky hull and a single mast , typically 15 to 25 meters in length, in use from ca. 1150 to 1500.
( historical ) The hypothetical precursor ship type of the above said to be in use during the early Middle Ages , variously alleged to be Frisian or Scandinavian .
( by extension ) A small fishing boat .
